1162
00:57:09,144 --> 00:57:12,279
A year?

1163
00:57:12,381 --> 00:57:14,414
Shame on you, Swanee.

1164
00:57:14,516 --> 00:57:15,949
Yes, you're right, Belle.

1165
00:57:19,087 --> 00:57:21,054
Shame on me, indeed.

1166
00:57:26,929 --> 00:57:28,895
Well, time to go.

1167
00:57:28,997 --> 00:57:30,564
What a divine evening.

1168
00:57:30,666 --> 00:57:32,732
We must do this again, real soon...

1169
00:57:32,834 --> 00:57:34,234
Say, at the turn of the century?

1170
00:57:37,639 --> 00:57:39,673
Rookie, Sadie, Morty.

1171
00:57:39,775 --> 00:57:41,274
Goodbye, Mr. Swann.

1172
00:57:41,376 --> 00:57:43,443
Belle.

1173
00:57:43,545 --> 00:57:45,812
Alan.

1174
00:57:45,914 --> 00:57:47,414
Oy vey.

1175
00:57:55,224 --> 00:57:57,757
Mr. and Mrs.
Kessler... apartment 4B.

1176
00:57:57,859 --> 00:57:59,192
God bless you, Mr. Swann.

1177
00:57:59,294 --> 00:58:01,361
Mr. and Mrs. Berkowitz,
apartment 2A... we love you.

1178
00:58:01,463 --> 00:58:04,431
Nathan and Lily Cantor,
second floor front... pleasure

1179
00:58:04,533 --> 00:58:05,699
to have you in the building.

1180
00:58:05,801 --> 00:58:08,101
Scalfoni, 1I...
You're the best.

1181
00:58:08,203 --> 00:58:09,703
How did you get into the building?

1182
00:58:09,805 --> 00:58:11,471
I'm the super.

1183
00:58:11,573 --> 00:58:12,305
Goodbye!

1184
00:58:12,407 --> 00:58:15,308
Goodbye!

1185
00:58:46,174 --> 00:58:48,942
