00:59:05,494 --> 00:59:06,526
Good, watch this.

1191
00:59:09,064 --> 00:59:10,064
Want to see it again?

1192
00:59:14,503 --> 00:59:18,171
Stone, you can either
watch me or join me.

1193
00:59:18,273 --> 00:59:19,739
One of them's more fun.

1194
00:59:19,841 --> 00:59:21,541
You were a hit in Brooklyn.

1195
00:59:21,643 --> 00:59:22,720
Want to try the Bronx next?

1196
00:59:22,744 --> 00:59:23,744
No.

1197
00:59:23,779 --> 00:59:26,346
1030 Park Avenue... the Downings.

1198
00:59:26,448 --> 00:59:27,714
No.

1199
00:59:27,816 --> 00:59:28,816
Please, no.

1200
00:59:28,850 --> 00:59:29,716
Let's not go there.

1201
00:59:29,818 --> 00:59:31,117
Why are we going there?

1202
00:59:31,219 --> 00:59:33,219
Why, to reweave the
fabric of your relationship

1203
00:59:33,322 --> 00:59:34,921
with the fair KC, that's why.

1204
00:59:35,023 --> 00:59:36,489
This surprise visit should do it.

1205
00:59:36,591 --> 00:59:39,359
I... I don't
think so, Mr. Swann.

1206
00:59:39,461 --> 00:59:41,594
KC Downing's parents
are having a big party.

1207
00:59:41,697 --> 00:59:43,963
Besides, they're not going to
let us up in that building.

1208
00:59:44,066 --> 00:59:45,732
Excellent.

1209
00:59:45,834 --> 00:59:47,033
Ever done any mountaineering?

1210
00:59:55,110 --> 01:00:01,781
Now all we have to do is
to get from here to there.

1211
01:00:01,883 --> 01:00:03,717
It won't work.

1212
01:00:03,819 --> 01:00:07,520
It worked perfectly well in
"A Slight Case of Divorce."

1213
01:00:07,622 --> 01:00:09,189
That was a movie.

1214
01:00:09,291 --> 01:00:11,291
This is real life.

1215
01:00:14,796 --> 01:00:18,264
What is the difference?

1216
01:00:18,367 --> 01:00:22,402
No.

1217
01:00:25,407 --> 01:00:28,007
It's stuck.

1218
01:00:31,146 --> 01:00:35,048
What we need is something like a rope.

1219
01:00:42,023 --> 01:00:43,623
Let's not do this.

1220
01:00:43,725 --> 01:00:46,459
Stone... I've done it 100 times!

1222
01:00:51,867 --> 01:00:53,767
Always had a stuntman.

1223
01:01:07,015 --> 01:01:08,015
Perfect.

1224
01:01:11,453 --> 01:01:12,886
Wait!

1225
01:01:12,988 --> 01:01:14,020
Wait, wait, wait!

1226
01:01:14,122 --> 01:01:14,988
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

1227
01:01:15,090 --> 01:01:16,189
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

1228
01:01:16,291 --> 01:01:18,725
Let's just go back to the way we came

1229
01:01:18,827 --> 01:01:20,860
and go through her front door.

1230
01:01:20,962 --> 01:01:22,295
Dull!

1231
01:01:22,397 --> 01:01:23,029
Boring!

1232
01:01:23,131 --> 01:01:25,231
Old hat.

1233
01:01:25,333 --> 01:01:27,200
Stone, the cardinal rule...

1234
01:01:27,302 --> 01:01:30,136
They always a big entrance!

1235
01:01:30,238 --> 01:01:31,671
I assure you this.

1236
01:01:38,380 --> 01:01:40,380
Does anybody die in these movies?

1237
01:01:40,482 --> 01:01:43,183
Die?

1238
01:01:43,285 --> 01:01:46,920
Of course not... it's just fun!

1239
01:01:47,022 --> 01:01:48,421
Fun?

1240
01:01:48,523 --> 01:01:50,156
Fun!

1241
01:01:50,258 --> 01:01:53,993
He thinks this is fun!

1242
01:01:56,398 --> 01:01:59,365
I'm going down. Now.

1243
01:02:00,569 --> 01:02:03,102
When I arrive, I shall
hold the rope taut,

1244
01:02:03,205 --> 01:02:04,537
and you can just shimmy down.

1245
01:02:04,639 --> 01:02:07,941
I'm not shimmying down anything.

1246
01:02:08,043 --> 01:02:10,009
It's too dangerous.

1247
01:02:10,111 --> 01:02:11,344
Nonsense!

1248
01:02:11,446 --> 01:02:13,713
Not when you've been
instructed by Niblick.

1249
01:02:18,086 --> 01:02:19,486
Who the hell is Niblick?

1250
01:02:19,588 --> 01:02:23,289
Niblick is my Sherpa
guide from the Himalayas.

1251
01:02:23,391 --> 01:02:27,627
The Himalayas... the Himalayas!

1252
01:02:27,729 --> 01:02:28,895
Look, there's the door.

1253
01:02:28,997 --> 01:02:30,597
Come on, let's go give it a try.

1254
01:02:34,870 --> 01:02:35,870
It's open!

1255
01:02:44,913 --> 01:02:46,746
My god.

1256
01:02:47,816 --> 01:02:49,115
I killed him.

1257
01:02:49,217 --> 01:02:52,819
I'm supposed to take care
of him and I killed him.

1258
01:02:52,921 --> 01:02:54,621
God!

1259
01:02:59,728 --> 01:03:01,227
The bond issue was a fraud.

1260
01:03:01,329 --> 01:03:03,496
The company went bankrupt.

1261
01:03:03,598 --> 01:03:04,976
They looked solid, but
they went belly up.

1262
01:03:05,000 --> 01:03:07,867
Excuse me, have you seen that film...

1263
01:03:07,969 --> 01:03:09,068
"Defender of the Crown"?

1264
01:03:09,170 --> 01:03:10,570
Just like that...

1265
01:03:10,672 --> 01:03:12,483
The film... "Defender of the
Crown"... have you seen it?

1266
01:03:12,507 --> 01:03:15,174
Starring... what's
that guy's name?

1267
01:03:15,277 --> 01:03:20,246
Alan... Alan... Swann.

1269
01:03:20,348 --> 01:03:22,115
Yeah, Alan Swann!

1270
01:03:22,217 --> 01:03:24,918
Bill, I think Alan Swann's beneath us.

1271
01:03:25,020 --> 01:03:27,020
Well, of course he's
beneath us, he's an actor.

1272
01:03:27,122 --> 01:03:28,221
No, I mean, I think Alan.

1273
01:03:28,323 --> 01:03:29,889
Swann's beneath us right now.

1274
01:03:29,991 --> 01:03:32,225
Look!

1275
01:03:32,327 --> 01:03:34,594
Harry, get the hell out here!

1276
01:03:34,696 --> 01:03:37,764
Alan Swann is hanging from...
Something from the roof!

1277
01:03:37,866 --> 01:03:39,432
- Pull!
- Pull him up!

1278
01:03:39,534 --> 01:03:40,199
Pull!

1279
01:03:40,302 --> 01:03:44,170
That's it, here he comes.

1280
01:03:44,272 --> 01:03:46,072
Good evening, do you have a light?

1281
01:03:46,174 --> 01:03:49,542
Help me, help me!

1282
01:03:49,644 --> 01:03:50,644
Terrace?

1283
01:03:56,217 --> 01:03:57,417
Well done.

1284
01:03:57,519 --> 01:03:59,385
We've just dropped in
to see the Downings.

1285
01:03:59,487 --> 01:04:01,387
There are no Downings here.

1286
01:04:01,489 --> 01:04:02,522
No Downings here?

1287
01:04:02,624 --> 01:04:03,624
No.

1288
01:04:07,095 --> 01:04:11,397
The Downing's are downstairs on 14.

1289
01:04:11,499 --> 01:04:15,268
Close, Stone, very close.

1290
01:04:15,370 --> 01:04:20,840
Mr. Swann, I think
I'm going to be unwell.

1291
01:04:20,942 --> 01:04:23,009
Stone, ladies are unwell.

1292
01:04:23,111 --> 01:04:25,178
Gentlemen vomit.

1293
01:04:28,917 --> 01:04:30,984
Alfredo, you needn't wait.

1294
01:04:31,086 --> 01:04:32,485
We shan't need the car anymore.

1295
01:04:32,587 --> 01:04:35,021
We're going to throw up in
the park and then walk home.

1296
01:05:04,452 --> 01:05:06,252
Mr. Swann, may
tell you something?

1297
01:05:07,722 --> 01:05:11,791
Benjy Stone is not who he seems to be.

1298
01:05:11,893 --> 01:05:13,493
Who is, Stone, who is?

1299
01:05:13,595 --> 01:05:16,429
But I'm not even Benjy Stone.

1300
01:05:16,531 --> 01:05:19,365
I'm Benjamin Steinberg.

1301
01:05:19,467 --> 01:05:21,112
I changed my name because
I thought it wouldn't

1302
01:05:21,136 --> 01:05:23,036
look good on the screen.

1303
01:05:23,138 --> 01:05:24,138
I'm a phony.

1304
01:05:24,172 --> 01:05:26,272
Because you changed your name?

1305
01:05:26,374 --> 01:05:28,274
What's in a name?

1306
01:05:28,376 --> 01:05:32,912
A rose by any other name
would wither and die.

1307
01:05:33,014 --> 01:05:36,249
I'll give you a name... Clarence Duffy.

1309
01:05:36,351 --> 01:05:38,317
Clarence Duffy?

1310
01:05:38,420 --> 01:05:39,886
Who's Clarence Duffy?

1311
01:05:39,988 --> 01:05:42,722
He's a young man from
the west of Scotland...

1312
01:05:42,824 --> 01:05:45,291
Middle-class, Irish
descent, whose father

1313
01:05:45,393 --> 01:05:47,326
was a grammar school teacher.

1314
01:05:47,429 --> 01:05:49,295
His mother looked after her garden,

1315
01:05:49,397 --> 01:05:52,131
her husband, and her only son.

1316
01:05:52,233 --> 01:05:54,634
At the age of 18, he joined the Navy.

1317
01:05:54,736 --> 01:05:57,603
One year later, he
jumped ship in Liverpool,

1318
01:05:57,706 --> 01:06:00,473
has notions of becoming an actor,

1319
01:06:00,575 --> 01:06:03,042
finishes up in English "B" movies.

1320
01:06:03,144 --> 01:06:06,512
Six months later, Lou
Goldmark of Paramount Studios

1321
01:06:06,614 --> 01:06:10,049
announces his find, a
dashing new English actor

1322
01:06:10,151 --> 01:06:12,952
to star in Paramount's
next big adventure film...

1323
01:06:13,054 --> 01:06:15,221
"Swords of Glory."

1324
01:06:15,323 --> 01:06:16,522
Clarence Duffy.

1325
01:06:16,624 --> 01:06:17,690
One and the same.

1326
01:06:17,792 --> 01:06:20,093
And you're not Allen Swann.

1327
01:06:20,195 --> 01:06:21,761
Yes, I am.

1328
01:06:25,834 --> 01:06:29,368
And you're the only
living soul who knows it.

1329
01:06:29,471 --> 01:06:31,571
It dies with me, Clarence.

1330
01:06:36,411 --> 01:06:37,543
At least you're an actor.

1331
01:06:37,645 --> 01:06:38,956
Actors are supposed to make up names.

1332
01:06:38,980 --> 01:06:41,914
It's not just making
up a name, Stoneberg.

1333
01:06:42,016 --> 01:06:44,317
The studio made up an entire life for me,

1334
01:06:44,419 --> 01:06:45,918
and I let them do it.

1335
01:06:46,020 --> 01:06:48,332
And now I can't tell where the
bogus one ends and the real one

1336
01:06:48,356 --> 01:06:49,522
begins.

1337
01:06:49,624 --> 01:06:51,924
Nothing about me is what it seems to be,

1338
01:06:52,026 --> 01:06:54,694
even the reason I'm doing your
"Comedy Cavalcade" program.

1339
01:06:54,796 --> 01:06:56,529
It's not because I wanted to.

1340
01:06:56,631 --> 01:06:58,397
It's a deal I made with my new partner,

1341
01:06:58,500 --> 01:07:00,466
the Internal Revenue Service.

1342
01:07:00,568 --> 01:07:02,802
If I do the show and give
them half the proceeds,

1343
01:07:02,904 --> 01:07:05,571
they promise not to throw
me out of the country.

1344
01:07:05,673 --> 01:07:07,907
Well, that dies with me, too, Duff.

1345
01:07:08,009 --> 01:07:10,343
Tonight, your mother
said, "shame on you,"

1346
01:07:10,445 --> 01:07:11,878
and she was right.

1347
01:07:11,980 --> 01:07:14,614
I'm fed up with people letting
me get away with things,

1348
01:07:14,716 --> 01:07:16,749
and everybody does...
My friends, my agent,

1349
01:07:16,851 --> 01:07:18,451
my manager, my doctors...

1350
01:07:18,553 --> 01:07:20,052
my former wives, even my daughter.

1351
01:07:23,758 --> 01:07:27,693
Haven't we walked enough for one night?

1352
01:07:27,796 --> 01:07:29,495
No... The horse, Stoneberg!

1354
01:07:29,597 --> 01:07:30,696
No, no, no, no!

1355
01:07:30,799 --> 01:07:31,864
No!

1356
01:07:37,572 --> 01:07:40,840
You'll get 30 years for this.

1357
01:07:52,287 --> 01:07:53,019
Hey!

1358
01:07:53,121 --> 01:07:54,121
Hey!

1359
01:08:42,136 --> 01:08:43,136
No!

1360
01:09:41,996 --> 01:09:42,595
Tess!

1361
01:09:42,697 --> 01:09:44,463
Who's Tess?

